00:23:46,124 --> 00:23:48,092
To teach theology?

257
00:23:48,159 --> 00:23:49,854
He undermines the prince.

258
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:52,624
Come on, there is no
clear teaching on relics.

259
00:23:52,697 --> 00:23:54,028
When I became a monk,

260
00:23:54,098 --> 00:23:56,999
I believed the monk's cowl
would make me holy.

261
00:23:57,068 --> 00:23:59,866
Was I an arrogant fool?

262
00:24:00,872 --> 00:24:03,306
Now they have made me
a doctor of divinity,

263
00:24:03,374 --> 00:24:07,902
and I'm tempted to believe
that this scholar's robe

264
00:24:07,979 --> 00:24:09,640
will make me wise.

265
00:24:09,714 --> 00:24:13,707
Well, God once spoke
through the mouth of an ass.

266
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:16,879
Perhaps he's about to
do so again.

267
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:19,788
But I'll tell you straight
what I think.

268
00:24:23,227 --> 00:24:24,854
Who here has been to Rome?

269
00:24:26,097 --> 00:24:28,463
Did you buy an indulgence?

270
00:24:28,533 --> 00:24:29,830
No.

271
00:24:29,901 --> 00:24:31,391
I did.

272
00:24:33,204 --> 00:24:36,765
For a silver florin, I freed
my grandfather from Purgatory.

273
00:24:40,678 --> 00:24:44,136
For twice that, I could have sprung
grandma and Uncle Marcus too,

274
00:24:44,215 --> 00:24:47,241
but I didn't have the funds,
so they had to stay in the hot place.

275
00:24:47,318 --> 00:24:49,479
As for myself,
the priests assured me

276
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:51,613
that by gazing at sacred relics,

277
00:24:51,689 --> 00:24:54,021
I could cut down
my time in Purgatory.

278
00:24:54,092 --> 00:24:56,788
Luckily for me, Rome had
enough nails from the Holy Cross

279
00:24:56,861 --> 00:24:59,386
to shoe every horse in Saxony.

280
00:25:00,398 --> 00:25:04,232
But there are relics
elsewhere in Christendom.

281
00:25:04,302 --> 00:25:08,602
Eighteen out of twelve apostles
are buried in Spain.

282
00:25:09,674 --> 00:25:11,608
And yet here in Wittenberg,

283
00:25:11,676 --> 00:25:14,236
we have the pick of the crop...

284
00:25:14,312 --> 00:25:16,075
bread from the Last Supper,

285
00:25:16,147 --> 00:25:18,513
milk from the Mirgin's breast,

286
00:25:18,583 --> 00:25:21,746
a thorn that pierced
Christ's brow on Calvary,

287
00:25:21,819 --> 00:25:25,516
and 19,000 other bits
of sacred bone,

288
00:25:25,590 --> 00:25:28,286
all authenticated sacred relics.

289
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:29,951
Even John Tetzel himself...

290
00:25:31,963 --> 00:25:35,023
Inquisitor of Poland and Saxony,

291
00:25:35,099 --> 00:25:38,796
seller of indulgences
extraordinary,

292
00:25:38,870 --> 00:25:44,274
connoisseur of relics,
envies oun collection:

293
00:25:44,342 --> 00:25:47,334
To possess them
for a single night,

294
00:25:47,412 --> 00:25:52,145
he would willingly surrender
five years of his earthly life:

295
00:25:58,356 --> 00:26:00,950
Or 500 years in Purgatory.

296
00:26:06,330 --> 00:26:09,993
And now, good citizens
of Wittenberg,

297
00:26:10,068 --> 00:26:14,664
Prince Frederick of Saxony
invites you here to his courtyard

298
00:26:14,739 --> 00:26:17,970
to witness a mystery play

299
00:26:18,042 --> 00:26:22,638
on that ever most popular
of subjects...

300
00:26:22,713 --> 00:26:26,513
the Day of Judgment.

301
00:26:39,330 --> 00:26:41,195
Just like old times, Martin.

302
00:26:43,501 --> 00:26:45,162
Excellency.

303
00:26:47,004 --> 00:26:47,993
Secretary.

304
00:26:48,072 --> 00:26:49,835
Prince's secretary.

305
00:26:49,907 --> 00:26:53,434
Such secretaries have a habit
of becoming Excellencies.

306
00:26:53,511 --> 00:26:57,208
Even when we were law students,
I had you marked for great things.

307
00:26:57,281 --> 00:27:00,216
I was hoping you may be
of some help in that regard.

308
00:27:00,284 --> 00:27:03,651
Prince Frederick is
exceedingly proud of his relics.

309
00:27:04,956 --> 00:27:07,390
Then I'm sorry
he didn't hear my lecture.

310
00:27:07,458 --> 00:27:09,449
Perhaps I could have swayed him.

311
00:27:10,528 --> 00:27:12,519
He spent 20 years
and a large fortune

312
00:27:12,597 --> 00:27:14,224
building his collection,

313
00:27:14,298 --> 00:27:16,630
that in a week's time,
on All Saints' Day,

314
00:27:16,701 --> 00:27:18,999
thousands of faithful Christians
are coming to see.

315
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:21,061
Paying to see.

316
00:27:21,139 --> 00:27:23,733
Contributions are
customary for indulgences,

317
00:27:23,808 --> 00:27:26,242
along with confession

318
00:27:26,310 --> 00:27:28,141
and true penitence.

319
00:27:30,815 --> 00:27:32,544
Ah, yes.

320
00:27:32,617 --> 00:27:34,209
The right prayers,
the right coins,

321
00:27:34,285 --> 00:27:41,054
and 1,900,202 years
and 27 days less in Purgatory.

322
00:27:41,125 --> 00:27:44,151
Do not bite the hand
that feeds you, Martin.

323
00:27:44,228 --> 00:27:48,324
Our prince pays
for your chair in this university.

324
00:27:49,834 --> 00:27:51,665
His relics pay for your chair.

325
00:27:55,006 --> 00:27:56,906
And he who pays the piper...

326
00:27:58,743 --> 00:28:00,335
calls the tune.

327
00:28:00,411 --> 00:28:02,606
Do not embarrass him.

328
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:06,548
No one is more delighted
with your popularity here.

329
00:28:10,154 --> 00:28:12,850
He'd prefer you stay.

330
00:28:24,769 --> 00:28:26,259
Master Kranauer,

331
00:28:26,337 --> 00:28:30,171
is Luther open to persuasion?

332
00:28:31,175 --> 00:28:33,803
Not likely, my prince.
He's as bitable as...

333
00:28:33,878 --> 00:28:35,573
As a donkey,
you were going to say?

334
00:28:35,646 --> 00:28:36,738
Indeed, indeed.

335
00:28:40,985 --> 00:28:45,752
I am conscious of the great honor
you do me, Cardinal Cajetan,

336
00:28:45,823 --> 00:28:48,121
in recommending me
to His Holiness.

337
00:28:48,192 --> 00:28:51,286
I doubt you'll think it an honor
20 years from now, Aleander.

338
00:28:51,362 --> 00:28:54,490
My first master
was Pope Alexander MI.

339
00:28:55,833 --> 00:28:58,324
Three mistresses,
five children,

340
00:28:58,402 --> 00:29:03,271
and a most fervent devotion
to bullfighting.

341
00:29:03,341 --> 00:29:05,309
Pope Julius ll...

342
00:29:05,376 --> 00:29:08,675
a month ago, he was
spiritual leader of the whole world.

343
00:29:08,746 --> 00:29:10,475
Quite dignified-looking, isn't he?

344
00:29:11,549 --> 00:29:13,039
But it's not
what Julius wanted.

345
00:29:13,117 --> 00:29:15,745
He wanted to be
remembered as a warrior,

346
00:29:15,820 --> 00:29:18,516
sitting on his horse,
sword in hand,

347
00:29:18,589 --> 00:29:20,489
besieging the Menetians.

348
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:25,226
What is it you seek, Aleander?

349
00:29:26,297 --> 00:29:27,491
To serve God.

350
00:29:29,467 --> 00:29:32,231
To serve him with all my heart.

351
00:29:32,303 --> 00:29:34,635
And that is
how you will be tempted.

352
00:30:32,096 --> 00:30:35,327
Pope Leo X,
sovereign bishop of Rome,

353
00:30:35,399 --> 00:30:36,957
successor to Saint Peter

354
00:30:37,034 --> 00:30:39,901
and holy head
of the Roman Catholic church.

355
00:30:40,905 --> 00:30:43,965
I've been longing for
someone to save Christendom.

356
00:30:47,878 --> 00:30:49,812
Let us pray he's come.

357
00:30:52,817 --> 00:30:55,342
Your reputation
precedes you, Aleander.

358
00:30:56,387 --> 00:30:57,786
Then I am fearful.

359
00:30:58,889 --> 00:31:01,585
Cardinal Cajetan says
you're a brilliant scholar,

360
00:31:01,659 --> 00:31:03,923
yet possess
a fervent desire to serve.

361
00:31:03,994 --> 00:31:06,519
I have need of such gifts.

362
00:31:06,597 --> 00:31:08,690
Excellency.

363
00:31:08,766 --> 00:31:12,202
Albert of Brandenburg wants
to be Archbishop of Mainz.

364
00:31:12,269 --> 00:31:16,365
He's already archbishop
of two German territories.

365
00:31:16,440 --> 00:31:17,429
Correct.

366
00:31:17,508 --> 00:31:20,306
Then canon law disqualifies him
from holding a third.

367
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:25,645
Moreover, wasn't he underage
when granted his first post?

368
00:31:25,716 --> 00:31:26,978
Just so.

369
00:31:28,152 --> 00:31:29,881
Even as I myself was.

370
00:31:29,954 --> 00:31:32,787
Doubtless Cajetan has informed you

371
00:31:32,857 --> 00:31:36,054
that I was made cardinal
at the age of 13.

372
00:31:36,127 --> 00:31:39,585
Albert's ambition
could still serve God's glory.

373
00:31:39,663 --> 00:31:41,187
The Turks at the gates of Mienna.

374
00:31:42,199 --> 00:31:44,030
The French are
yapping at my heels,

375
00:31:44,101 --> 00:31:46,092
and Rome itself has
become an open sewer

376
00:31:46,170 --> 00:31:49,298
filled with wild dogs
and cats by day

377
00:31:49,373 --> 00:31:51,739
and brigands
and fornicators by night.

378
00:31:54,412 --> 00:31:56,744
And this new
Basilica of Saint Peter's,

379
00:31:56,814 --> 00:31:59,715
it's not just a building,
Aleander,

380
00:31:59,784 --> 00:32:04,221
it's a symbol of my intent
to restore Christ's church.

381
00:32:07,158 --> 00:32:09,854
And Albert could be
a minor blessing in that.

382
00:32:11,162 --> 00:32:13,426
He offers 10,000 ducats
for Mainz.

383
00:32:14,498 --> 00:32:16,693
But Albert is bankrupt.

384
00:32:16,767 --> 00:32:18,132
You're well-informed.

385
00:32:19,837 --> 00:32:22,101
The Fuggers will
lend him the money.

386
00:32:22,173 --> 00:32:24,164
The imperial bankers?

387
00:32:25,676 --> 00:32:27,143
An eight-year loan.

388
00:32:27,211 --> 00:32:29,805
And how
would he repay them?

389
00:32:33,851 --> 00:32:35,284
John Tetzel.

390
00:32:37,788 --> 00:32:41,019
There, that's him:
Father John Tetzel:

391
00:32:43,394 --> 00:32:47,125
Don't unfurl the banners
until the fire ignites.

392
00:32:47,198 --> 00:32:50,565
Everything has been prepared
exactly as you instructed.

393
00:33:00,377 --> 00:33:02,072
Welcome, Father Tetzel:

394
00:33:03,147 --> 00:33:04,307
Come on, people:

395
00:33:11,155 --> 00:33:12,179
Gather round:

396
00:33:30,007 --> 00:33:31,634
Good people of Juterbog...

397
00:33:32,843 --> 00:33:35,607
have you ever burned
your hand in the fire?

398
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:38,511
Even one finger
made raw by the flame

399
00:33:38,582 --> 00:33:40,675
will torment you
throughout the night.

400
00:33:40,751 --> 00:33:41,877
Is it not so?

401
00:33:41,952 --> 00:33:43,613
Yes:

402
00:33:59,703 --> 00:34:05,266
Imagine, then,
your entire body burning.

403
00:34:05,342 --> 00:34:07,139
Not for one sleepless night...

404
00:34:08,145 --> 00:34:09,305
not for a week,

405
00:34:09,380 --> 00:34:12,110
but for all eternity:

406
00:34:12,182 --> 00:34:15,709
Are we to be spared
the fires of damnation

407
00:34:15,786 --> 00:34:17,413
on the Judgment Day?

408
00:34:25,829 --> 00:34:31,392
Tonight, your Pope,
the vicar of Christ, sends you a gift,

409
00:34:31,468 --> 00:34:34,767
a gift to save you
from such fires,

410
00:34:34,838 --> 00:34:38,069
a special indulgence granted

411
00:34:38,142 --> 00:34:41,043
for the building
of Saint Peter's Church in Rome...

412
00:34:43,047 --> 00:34:46,744
where the bones
of the apostles lie moldering,

413
00:34:46,817 --> 00:34:49,251
exposed to wind and rain,

414
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:52,221
desecrated by wild animals.

415
00:34:52,289 --> 00:34:56,851
Take heed the words
of your Holy Father who says,

416
00:34:56,927 --> 00:34:59,862
"Lay a stone for Saint Peter's,

417
00:34:59,930 --> 00:35:03,923
"and you lay the foundation
for your own salvation

418
00:35:04,001 --> 00:35:05,593
and happiness in heaven."

419
00:35:05,669 --> 00:35:09,605
How? With this indulgence.

420
00:35:09,673 --> 00:35:12,335
When? Tonight,

421
00:35:12,409 --> 00:35:14,900
and only tonight.

422
00:35:14,979 --> 00:35:17,777
Seek the Lord while he is near.

423
00:35:17,848 --> 00:35:19,907
Here is your raft.

424
00:35:19,984 --> 00:35:21,849
Take hold:

425
00:35:42,673 --> 00:35:46,074
In Heaven, there is
a treasure chest filled with merit.

426
00:35:47,411 --> 00:35:50,141
Merit from Christ Jesus,

427
00:35:50,214 --> 00:35:52,774
the Mirgin Mary, and the saints,

428
00:35:52,850 --> 00:35:55,011
who, through their holy lives,

429
00:35:55,085 --> 00:35:59,988
have merit to spare
for us poor sinners in need.

430
00:36:01,725 --> 00:36:04,387
Tonight, that treasury
is open to you.

431
00:36:06,764 --> 00:36:08,994
Do you not hear their voices,

432
00:36:09,066 --> 00:36:11,296
the screaming voices?

433
00:36:12,970 --> 00:36:14,801
Your deceased parents.

434
00:36:15,806 --> 00:36:16,966
Grandparents.

435
00:36:17,975 --> 00:36:22,173
Uncles, aunts screaming.

436
00:36:23,247 --> 00:36:24,737
Beloved child.

437
00:36:26,316 --> 00:36:27,943
Beloved child.

438
00:36:29,153 --> 00:36:30,950
Because, for a few coins,

439
00:36:31,021 --> 00:36:35,549
you can rescue them
from their punishments and pain.

440
00:36:36,994 --> 00:36:37,983
Listen.

441
00:36:38,062 --> 00:36:39,996
Open your ears.

442
00:36:41,298 --> 00:36:43,391
Father calling to son,

443
00:36:43,467 --> 00:36:45,992
mother to daughter.

444
00:36:47,171 --> 00:36:49,901
When a coin
in the coffer rings,

445
00:36:49,973 --> 00:36:52,806
the soul
from Purgatory springs.

446
00:36:55,479 --> 00:37:00,246
God-fearing man,
do you have a coin for Christ?

447
00:37:00,317 --> 00:37:01,875
Yes.

448
00:37:16,200 --> 00:37:17,462
Gentle mother...

449
00:37:19,970 --> 00:37:22,962
when the time comes,
make certain your crippled child

450
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,099
can run to Jesus.

451
00:37:30,881 --> 00:37:33,406
These learned monks
are standing by

452
00:37:33,484 --> 00:37:35,247
to write down your name

453
00:37:35,319 --> 00:37:38,482
or the name of a loved one,
dead or alive, on this...

454
00:37:39,523 --> 00:37:43,823
your passport to
the celestial joys of Paradise.

455
00:37:52,102 --> 00:37:53,091
Name?

456
00:38:21,365 --> 00:38:22,889
We can preach
until we're hoarse,

457
00:38:22,966 --> 00:38:25,161
but if we cannot bring the Christ
of the Gospels to our people...

458
00:38:25,235 --> 00:38:27,226
...what do we offer them?
- Dr. Martin:

459
00:38:34,978 --> 00:38:36,411
I did this for Grete.

460
00:38:40,818 --> 00:38:43,844
Issued by
the Archbishop of Mainz.

461
00:38:49,827 --> 00:38:51,226
Where did you get this?

462
00:38:51,295 --> 00:38:55,163
Juterbog.
I bought it in the church.

463
00:38:57,334 --> 00:38:59,234
It's just paper, Hanna.

464
00:39:00,771 --> 00:39:02,261
These words mean...

465
00:39:04,308 --> 00:39:05,605
nothing.

466
00:39:08,178 --> 00:39:09,611
It's no good?

467
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:12,410
You must put your trust
in God's love.

468
00:39:12,482 --> 00:39:14,074
Save your money

469
00:39:14,151 --> 00:39:15,778
to feed Grete.

470
