484
00:40:22,252 --> 00:40:25,517
why would he not do so
out of love rather than for money?"

485
00:40:29,693 --> 00:40:31,854
My God, who is this Martin Luther?

486
00:40:31,929 --> 00:40:34,796
- Fritz:
- What?

487
00:40:34,865 --> 00:40:36,856
Dr. Luther wanted
everyone to see that:

488
00:40:36,934 --> 00:40:38,595
And everyone will.

489
00:40:42,873 --> 00:40:44,864
Good people of Magdeburg,

490
00:40:44,942 --> 00:40:48,309
take hold of the raft
while you still can.

491
00:40:48,378 --> 00:40:51,541
So much grace
for so little coin:

492
00:40:58,388 --> 00:41:00,356
German money
for the German church.

493
00:41:00,424 --> 00:41:03,154
Does Saint Peter lie
in a German church?

494
00:41:03,226 --> 00:41:05,490
- Or Saint Paul?
- We don't need your saints.

495
00:41:05,562 --> 00:41:07,689
Or any of the holy apostles?

496
00:41:10,133 --> 00:41:14,126
With this indulgence,
I can absolve any sin.

497
00:41:14,204 --> 00:41:16,764
I can even save the soul of the man

498
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:19,968
who violates
the mother of God herself.

499
00:41:25,449 --> 00:41:28,111
One-fifth of the usual take.

500
00:41:28,185 --> 00:41:30,779
How will you
explain this to Rome?

501
00:41:30,854 --> 00:41:32,287
Damn that heretic:

502
00:41:33,857 --> 00:41:36,087
He will burn in hell.

503
00:41:36,159 --> 00:41:38,650
This drunken little German monk

504
00:41:38,729 --> 00:41:41,789
is intoxicated with himself.

505
00:41:47,371 --> 00:41:48,531
Sober him.

506
00:41:58,382 --> 00:42:00,179
Why was Prince Frederick
not apprised

507
00:42:00,250 --> 00:42:01,979
of your letter
to Albert of Mainz?

508
00:42:02,986 --> 00:42:04,476
Why?

509
00:42:04,554 --> 00:42:06,249
I did not want him compromised.

510
00:42:07,824 --> 00:42:09,758
Now our prince
can swear before God

511
00:42:09,826 --> 00:42:11,418
he had no knowledge
of my writings

512
00:42:11,495 --> 00:42:13,360
or my criticism
of the Archbishop.

513
00:42:13,430 --> 00:42:16,024
Criticism of the Archbishop?
What of your criticism of Rome?

514
00:42:16,099 --> 00:42:18,431
Do you have any idea
how embarrassing this is

515
00:42:18,502 --> 00:42:19,764
to Prince Frederick,

516
00:42:19,836 --> 00:42:21,269
his prize professor of theology

517
00:42:21,338 --> 00:42:23,135
drawing condemnation
from the Pope?

518
00:42:23,206 --> 00:42:26,573
My criticism was not
of the Holy Father himself,

519
00:42:26,643 --> 00:42:29,339
but of those rogues
who claim to represent him.

520
00:42:34,618 --> 00:42:38,076
You have been summoned
to appear by Rome.

521
00:42:38,155 --> 00:42:40,521
You are threatened
with excommunication.

522
00:42:44,194 --> 00:42:45,957
But I'm a loyal son
of the church:

523
00:42:46,029 --> 00:42:47,963
I don't believe the Pope
would issue such a summons.

524
00:42:48,031 --> 00:42:49,896
Welcome to the world
of politics, Doctor.

525
00:42:51,368 --> 00:42:52,562
Martin...

526
00:42:56,873 --> 00:42:58,306
Lay low.

527
00:42:58,375 --> 00:43:00,570
Do not write
a single word to anyone

528
00:43:00,644 --> 00:43:02,908
until I have a chance
to sort this out.

529
00:43:04,848 --> 00:43:09,080
They've already published
my explanations of the 95 Tleses.

530
00:43:09,152 --> 00:43:11,620
I dedicated it to Pope Leo.

531
00:43:16,393 --> 00:43:19,157
Clearly, clearly
you've heard the rumors...

532
00:43:20,163 --> 00:43:22,597
that the Pope has
summoned me to Augsburg.

533
00:43:22,666 --> 00:43:23,826
Well, it's true.

534
00:43:25,836 --> 00:43:28,805
It's true, and I pray fervently

535
00:43:28,872 --> 00:43:30,999
he will find no fault with me.

536
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:36,136
But think on this
while I am gone.

537
00:43:39,182 --> 00:43:42,640
We obsess...

538
00:43:44,187 --> 00:43:45,677
over relics.

539
00:43:46,690 --> 00:43:48,317
Indulgences.

540
00:43:48,391 --> 00:43:50,484
Pilgrimages to holy places.

541
00:43:52,696 --> 00:43:56,359
Yet all the time,
all the time, there is Christ.

542
00:43:56,433 --> 00:43:59,561
Christ. Christ, here...

543
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:02,905
in every corner,

544
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:04,702
in every hour of the day.

545
00:44:04,774 --> 00:44:08,870
He isn't found
in the bones of saints...

546
00:44:09,980 --> 00:44:12,972
but here,
in your love for each other,

547
00:44:13,049 --> 00:44:15,040
in your love for one another...

548
00:44:16,052 --> 00:44:17,576
in His sacraments,

549
00:44:17,654 --> 00:44:20,555
and in God's holy word.

550
00:44:20,624 --> 00:44:26,062
If we, if we live the word,
by faith...

551
00:44:31,168 --> 00:44:34,604
in love

552
00:44:34,671 --> 00:44:38,869
and service to one another,

553
00:44:38,942 --> 00:44:42,605
we need fear
no man's judgment.

554
00:44:51,154 --> 00:44:53,019
- Good to see you.
- Thank you.

555
00:44:53,089 --> 00:44:55,557
Martin, the faculty
stands behind you.

556
00:44:56,560 --> 00:44:58,118
I have written a letter of protest,

557
00:44:58,195 --> 00:45:00,561
and I'll be the first to sign
should they arrest you in Augsburg.

558
00:45:00,630 --> 00:45:02,257
Thank you, Carlstadt.
Thank you.

559
00:45:10,874 --> 00:45:13,206
Bless you. Bless you.

560
00:45:16,913 --> 00:45:17,902
Father.

561
00:45:17,981 --> 00:45:19,471
Are you in trouble?

562
00:45:23,687 --> 00:45:25,985
What happens now?

563
00:45:27,057 --> 00:45:28,820
I honestly don't know.

564
00:45:31,328 --> 00:45:32,420
Well...

565
00:45:33,496 --> 00:45:35,760
Father, thank you.

566
00:45:35,832 --> 00:45:37,595
Thank you, Father.

567
00:45:37,667 --> 00:45:39,862
Just try to keep
your big mouth shut.

568
00:46:31,354 --> 00:46:32,844
Father.

569
00:46:32,922 --> 00:46:35,891
She wants you to know
that she prays for you every night.

570
00:47:23,673 --> 00:47:25,573
Father.

571
00:47:29,979 --> 00:47:30,968
Have I...?

572
00:47:35,485 --> 00:47:37,749
Have I caused you trouble too?

573
00:47:37,821 --> 00:47:39,652
I'm here
to get you through this.

574
00:47:40,824 --> 00:47:42,416
They've stopped
Tetzel from preaching.

575
00:47:42,492 --> 00:47:44,858
He's in Leipzig
under house arrest.

576
00:47:44,928 --> 00:47:47,226
That's a good sign, isn't it?
That means that Rome must understand.

577
00:47:47,297 --> 00:47:49,390
It just means he went too far.

578
00:47:51,134 --> 00:47:52,362
Martin.

579
00:47:52,435 --> 00:47:53,925
Martin, listen to me.

580
00:47:54,003 --> 00:47:56,096
Cardinal Cajetan
didn't bring you here

581
00:47:56,172 --> 00:47:58,140
to teach him the Scriptures.

582
00:47:58,208 --> 00:48:00,972
I beg you in God's name
to have a care.

583
00:48:01,044 --> 00:48:02,375
Be temperate.

584
00:48:02,445 --> 00:48:05,005
Don't talk, just listen.

585
00:48:05,081 --> 00:48:08,050
Your life
could depend on it.

586
00:48:08,118 --> 00:48:10,245
He's waiting for you.

587
00:48:41,484 --> 00:48:45,147
I am Girolamo Aleander,
representing Cardinal Cajetan.

588
00:48:46,156 --> 00:48:50,456
Your meeting won't take long.
I'm here to prepare you for tonight.

589
00:48:52,595 --> 00:48:53,584
Please.

590
00:48:55,165 --> 00:48:56,154
Sit.

591
00:49:06,376 --> 00:49:09,868
It was never my intention

592
00:49:09,946 --> 00:49:16,351
to say anything against
the honor and the dignity

593
00:49:16,419 --> 00:49:18,284
of our Holy Father.

594
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:22,057
Of course not, Brother Martin.

595
00:49:24,227 --> 00:49:26,127
And that being the case,

596
00:49:26,196 --> 00:49:28,255
that we all desire peace,

597
00:49:28,331 --> 00:49:33,826
you only have to follow a few
simple rules of protocol.

598
00:49:35,438 --> 00:49:36,905
When you meet the Cardinal,

599
00:49:36,973 --> 00:49:39,908
you will throw yourself on the floor,
face to the ground.

600
00:49:39,976 --> 00:49:43,207
The Cardinal will tell you to stand,
at which time you will kneel

601
00:49:43,279 --> 00:49:46,544
and remain kneeling
throughout your hearing.

602
00:49:48,651 --> 00:49:50,016
Do you understand?

603
00:49:50,086 --> 00:49:51,417
Yes.

604
00:49:52,489 --> 00:49:56,084
If the church takes exception
to a single point,

605
00:49:56,159 --> 00:49:58,150
I will submit to her immediately.

606
00:49:58,228 --> 00:50:02,255
But I'm sure when the Cardinal
and Pope Leo

607
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:03,663
understand my position...

608
00:50:05,335 --> 00:50:07,235
they'll find no fault with me.

609
00:50:11,407 --> 00:50:13,466
We have a misunderstanding.

610
00:50:14,511 --> 00:50:17,105
There will be no discussion.

611
00:50:19,182 --> 00:50:20,342
No debate.

612
00:50:23,853 --> 00:50:26,413
You have one word to say
and one word only.

613
00:50:27,490 --> 00:50:28,752
Revoco...

614
00:50:28,825 --> 00:50:30,793
I recant...

615
00:50:30,860 --> 00:50:32,555
and the matter is over.

616
00:50:34,364 --> 00:50:36,764
I think we do have
a misunderstanding.

617
00:50:36,833 --> 00:50:39,461
I came to Augsburg
to warn the Pope

618
00:50:39,536 --> 00:50:42,061
about the abuses
against the faithful

619
00:50:42,138 --> 00:50:43,969
by the indulgence preachers.

620
00:50:44,040 --> 00:50:45,473
Have a care, Brother Martin.

621
00:50:45,542 --> 00:50:47,305
It is the Pope who shall decide

622
00:50:47,377 --> 00:50:49,572
what is or is not
beneficial to Christendom.

623
00:50:51,814 --> 00:50:55,750
This evening, one word.

624
00:50:58,054 --> 00:50:59,043
Revoco.

625
00:51:02,825 --> 00:51:05,225
Thank you, Excellency.

626
00:51:13,002 --> 00:51:14,264
Brother Martin...

627
00:51:17,006 --> 00:51:20,305
with your permission,
I'm going to arrange a bath for you.

628
00:51:22,512 --> 00:51:24,173
Thank you, Excellency.

629
00:51:31,321 --> 00:51:33,482
My son, I know you desire

630
00:51:33,556 --> 00:51:36,787
to be a faithful servant
of Christ and His church.

631
00:51:36,859 --> 00:51:38,451
I am here to help you.

632
00:51:41,364 --> 00:51:43,798
Stand on your feet, my son.

633
00:51:51,374 --> 00:51:53,205
What do you have to say?

634
00:51:55,445 --> 00:51:57,174
Have I erred?

635
00:51:57,246 --> 00:52:00,272
Yes, you have erred.

636
00:52:00,350 --> 00:52:01,715
How?

637
00:52:04,187 --> 00:52:06,485
That I may avoid such error again.

638
00:52:06,556 --> 00:52:09,650
You have erred
by teaching new doctrines.

639
00:52:09,726 --> 00:52:12,718
Which of my teachings
is offensive to Rome?

640
00:52:12,795 --> 00:52:14,194
For one, indulgences.

641
00:52:14,263 --> 00:52:16,595
Pope Clement's decree,
Unigenitus.

642
00:52:16,666 --> 00:52:19,601
clearly states that
the merits of Christ

643
00:52:19,669 --> 00:52:21,830
are a treasure of indulgences.

644
00:52:21,904 --> 00:52:22,893
Acquire.

645
00:52:22,972 --> 00:52:25,668
I'm sorry, Your Grace.

646
00:52:25,742 --> 00:52:27,300
I think you'll find it says...

647
00:52:28,678 --> 00:52:32,842
"The merits of Christ acquire
the treasure of indulgences."

648
00:52:34,183 --> 00:52:36,083
I am not here
to wrangle with you.

649
00:52:36,152 --> 00:52:37,141
No, Your Grace.

650
00:52:37,220 --> 00:52:41,623
But Unigenitus was issued
175 years ago,

651
00:52:41,691 --> 00:52:44,785
and were this decree
not so embarrassing to our church,

652
00:52:44,861 --> 00:52:47,830
perhaps it would not be
commonly called Extnavagante

653
00:52:49,098 --> 00:52:51,999
and left out of
most collections of canon law.

654
00:52:52,068 --> 00:52:55,128
It contradicts Anommitanos.

655
00:52:55,204 --> 00:52:58,640
Our present Pope Leo is
in harmony with Clement's decree...

656
00:52:59,742 --> 00:53:01,369
and there ends the matter.

657
00:53:01,444 --> 00:53:04,038
The honor of the Papacy
is not preserved

658
00:53:04,113 --> 00:53:06,343
by the naked assertion
of Papal authority,

659
00:53:06,416 --> 00:53:09,249
but by safeguarding
the Pope's credibility

660
00:53:09,318 --> 00:53:11,912
and the clear testimonies
of divine Scripture.

661
00:53:11,988 --> 00:53:14,957
The Pope interprets Scripture.

662
00:53:15,024 --> 00:53:16,821
He may interpret it...

663
00:53:18,995 --> 00:53:20,553
but he is not above it.

664
00:53:20,630 --> 00:53:22,723
He was to say one word.

665
00:53:22,799 --> 00:53:24,960
We both know
the selling of indulgences

666
00:53:25,034 --> 00:53:27,025
have no Scriptural support.

667
00:53:27,103 --> 00:53:30,266
If common people could
read the Bible for themselves,

668
00:53:30,339 --> 00:53:32,273
they would understand
just how broad

669
00:53:32,341 --> 00:53:33,774
the church's interpretations are.

670
00:53:33,843 --> 00:53:35,333
That is outrageous:

671
00:53:36,345 --> 00:53:38,176
The Scriptures are too complex

672
00:53:38,247 --> 00:53:40,147
for even the average priest
to understand,

673
00:53:40,216 --> 00:53:41,706
much less the common man:

674
00:53:41,784 --> 00:53:43,877
Indulgences are
an established tradition

675
00:53:43,953 --> 00:53:46,649
which give comfort to
millions of simple Christians.

676
00:53:46,723 --> 00:53:49,453
Comfort? Your Grace,
I'm not interested in comfort.

677
00:53:49,525 --> 00:53:50,992
Comfort is not the issue:

678
00:53:51,060 --> 00:53:53,426
So you consider your discomfort

679
00:53:53,496 --> 00:53:56,488
more important than
the survival of Christianity?

680
00:53:56,566 --> 00:53:59,296
- I'm interested in the truth:
- The truth?

681
00:53:59,368 --> 00:54:02,235
The Turks are building armies
on our eastern borders.

682
00:54:02,305 --> 00:54:04,068
We are on the brink of war.

683
00:54:04,140 --> 00:54:07,735
To the west, lies a world of souls
who have never heard the name of Christ.

684
00:54:07,810 --> 00:54:09,402
That is the truth:

685
00:54:09,479 --> 00:54:11,777
Christianity is tearing apart,

686
00:54:11,848 --> 00:54:14,578
and just when we need
unity most,

687
00:54:14,650 --> 00:54:16,174
you create confusion:

688
00:54:16,252 --> 00:54:18,743
My goal is not to quarrel
with the Pope or the church,

689
00:54:18,821 --> 00:54:22,086
but to defend them
with more than mere opinion.

690
00:54:22,158 --> 00:54:25,389
The Gospel cannot be denied
for the word of man.

691
00:54:28,498 --> 00:54:30,932
I refuse to argue
with that monk.

692
00:54:32,368 --> 00:54:34,393
You said he was a simpleton.

693
00:54:34,470 --> 00:54:37,530
He questioned
the Pope's authority.

694
00:54:38,674 --> 00:54:40,938
Anommitanos.

695
00:54:41,010 --> 00:54:42,272
Unigenitus.

696
00:54:42,345 --> 00:54:46,782
Or shall we call it Extnavagante
like the rest of the world?

697
00:54:46,849 --> 00:54:48,339
He's a heretic.

698
00:54:50,520 --> 00:54:52,249
Our orders were clear.

699
00:54:53,856 --> 00:54:55,187
Either he recant...

700
00:54:56,192 --> 00:54:58,251
Do not presume
to lecture me, Aleander.

701
00:54:59,328 --> 00:55:01,455
I know perfectly well
what our orders were.

702
00:55:03,933 --> 00:55:06,629
I kept my temper and merely asked
to be shown the error of my ways.

703
00:55:06,702 --> 00:55:09,637
If you do not recant, you will be
delivered to the Inquisition.

704
00:55:09,705 --> 00:55:12,469
Will you recant?

705
00:55:13,476 --> 00:55:14,465
What?

706
00:55:19,315 --> 00:55:21,875
Then there is only one way
to save your life.

707
00:55:24,153 --> 00:55:25,142
Kneel.

708
00:55:26,389 --> 00:55:28,380
Kneel:

709
00:55:28,457 --> 00:55:29,856
Martin Luther,

710
00:55:29,926 --> 00:55:33,418
in the name of Christ,
I release you from your vows

711
00:55:33,496 --> 00:55:35,054
to the Augustinian order

712
00:55:35,131 --> 00:55:37,497
and commend you to God's mercy.

713
00:55:37,567 --> 00:55:40,627
I'm no longer your father,
do you understand?

714
00:55:40,703 --> 00:55:43,103
Were I your father,
then under canon law,

715
00:55:43,172 --> 00:55:46,266
I would be obligated to
deliver you to the authorities:

716
00:55:48,344 --> 00:55:51,313
But I'll be
your spiritual father...

717
00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:55,977
until the day I die.

718
00:56:03,125 --> 00:56:05,719
Now go.

719
00:56:05,795 --> 00:56:07,285
Go quickly:

720
00:56:08,798 --> 00:56:11,392
There is a horse at the back gate.

721
00:56:11,467 --> 00:56:14,231
Don't leave me alone,
Father. Please.

722
00:56:14,303 --> 00:56:15,292
Father:

723
00:56:34,657 --> 00:56:36,147
My pnince.

724
00:56:36,492 --> 00:56:37,652
how shall I answer?

725
00:56:38,661 --> 00:56:42,153
The Cardinal demands
that Luther be delivered to Rome

726
00:56:42,231 --> 00:56:43,721
or banished from Saxony.

727
00:56:44,834 --> 00:56:47,394
Have you read Luther's work?

728
00:56:48,671 --> 00:56:50,434
Yes, all of it.

729
00:56:50,506 --> 00:56:52,940
Yes. He's a brilliant
little monk, isn't he,

730
00:56:53,009 --> 00:56:55,341
with an independent mind.

731
00:56:56,512 --> 00:56:58,070
Yes, he is.

732
00:56:59,181 --> 00:57:02,514
Oh, Spalatin, you were
at law school with him, weren't you?

733
00:57:02,585 --> 00:57:05,076
Did he show any inclination then

734
00:57:05,154 --> 00:57:10,524
of surrender to influence?

735
00:57:10,593 --> 00:57:11,582
No.

736
00:57:11,661 --> 00:57:15,597
After all, all he has done
is to debate, eloquently,

737
00:57:15,665 --> 00:57:17,792
on a most interesting subject.

738
00:57:17,867 --> 00:57:19,198
And, after all,

739
00:57:19,268 --> 00:57:23,500
that is all one can ask
a good university professor to do.

740
00:57:25,441 --> 00:57:27,807
So what shall we say
to the Cardinal?

741
00:57:34,650 --> 00:57:36,083
Nothing.

742
00:57:36,152 --> 00:57:39,087
My lord, we have to respond.

743
00:57:39,155 --> 00:57:41,419
Spalatin, there are
two ways of saying no

744
00:57:41,490 --> 00:57:44,288
to someone you believe to be
stronger than yourself.

745
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:47,420
The first is to say nothing

746
00:57:47,496 --> 00:57:51,262
and go on merely doing
what you were doing before,

747
00:57:51,334 --> 00:57:53,768
and pretend
that you never heard,

748
00:57:53,836 --> 00:57:59,775
allow time and inertia
to be your allies.

749
00:58:01,110 --> 00:58:02,372
And the second?

750
00:58:02,445 --> 00:58:08,179
And the second is to say no
in such a kind and thoughtful way

751
00:58:08,250 --> 00:58:10,718
it befuddles them.

752
00:58:10,786 --> 00:58:13,778
Naturally, if both
these strategies fail,

753
00:58:13,856 --> 00:58:16,689
there is nothing but to relent.

754
00:58:18,461 --> 00:58:20,725
Or to fight:

755
00:58:20,796 --> 00:58:23,390
And of course,
if you decide to fight,

756
00:58:23,466 --> 00:58:26,560
you also have to decide to win.

757
00:58:27,970 --> 00:58:32,407
No, I'm not going to
send my monk to Rome.

758
00:58:32,475 --> 00:58:35,069
They'll only kill him.

759
00:58:35,144 --> 00:58:37,408
It's so irritating.

760
00:58:37,480 --> 00:58:40,074
Who are they
to deprive my university

761
00:58:40,149 --> 00:58:41,776
of such a fine mind?

762
00:58:42,752 --> 00:58:45,983
Your little German monk
is still spewing filth at us.

763
00:58:47,056 --> 00:58:49,183
He has a new cartoon circulating.

764
00:58:50,226 --> 00:58:52,717
He calls you an ass
playing a harp, Cajetan.

765
00:58:56,432 --> 00:58:59,924
The point, Your Holiness,
is that he does not write in Latin.

766
00:59:00,002 --> 00:59:01,367
Luther writes in German.

767
00:59:01,437 --> 00:59:03,337
That is his sword.

768
00:59:04,407 --> 00:59:06,432
So he does not
play like a gentleman?

769
00:59:07,910 --> 00:59:10,378
Ordinary Germans
can quote his work.

770
00:59:11,414 --> 00:59:14,212
If we wait,
we might be too late.

771
00:59:14,283 --> 00:59:16,513
You exaggerate his importance.

772
00:59:16,585 --> 00:59:20,112
Besides, you told me yourself
you agree with his list of abuses.

773
00:59:20,189 --> 00:59:22,180
Some of his concerns
have long been held

774
00:59:22,258 --> 00:59:24,385
by those who love the church, yes.

775
00:59:25,461 --> 00:59:27,486
I don't suppose your little monk

776
00:59:27,563 --> 00:59:30,259
would be interested
in a cardinal's hat?

777
