no food, no sleep.

1228
01:38:54,169 --> 01:38:55,636
So if you could just tell me...

1229
01:38:55,704 --> 01:38:56,693
I...

1230
01:38:58,340 --> 01:39:00,240
I'm Luther.

1231
01:39:01,843 --> 01:39:03,743
Katharina von Bora.

1232
01:39:03,812 --> 01:39:05,211
Martin Luther.

1233
01:39:06,214 --> 01:39:07,613
But you know that already.

1234
01:39:09,785 --> 01:39:11,582
I'll take you to a shelter.

1235
01:39:28,370 --> 01:39:29,530
Who's there?

1236
01:39:36,378 --> 01:39:37,367
No.

1237
01:39:40,582 --> 01:39:42,447
Martin Luther?

1238
01:39:42,517 --> 01:39:44,178
My lord.

1239
01:39:45,253 --> 01:39:49,155
Well. We meet at last.

1240
01:39:54,563 --> 01:39:57,259
I dedicated this work
to you, my lord.

1241
01:39:57,365 --> 01:39:59,356
The translation
of the New Testament...

1242
01:40:00,702 --> 01:40:02,260
into our own language.

1243
01:40:02,337 --> 01:40:03,964
Into German?

1244
01:40:08,844 --> 01:40:13,076
But this will
separate us from Rome...

1245
01:40:14,149 --> 01:40:15,377
forever.

1246
01:40:16,451 --> 01:40:19,545
I have always
sought Christian unity,

1247
01:40:19,621 --> 01:40:22,556
but not at the price of servitude.

1248
01:40:22,624 --> 01:40:24,251
I answer to God's law,

1249
01:40:24,326 --> 01:40:26,123
not Roman.

1250
01:40:27,195 --> 01:40:29,663
Roman law is the reality.

1251
01:40:29,731 --> 01:40:31,494
I believe in the reality of Christ.

1252
01:40:31,566 --> 01:40:33,329
With no compromises?

1253
01:40:33,401 --> 01:40:34,663
None.

1254
01:40:38,974 --> 01:40:41,875
You realize, of course,
they'll take this to be

1255
01:40:41,943 --> 01:40:44,309
an act of sheer provocation.

1256
01:40:44,379 --> 01:40:45,710
Yes.

1257
01:40:45,780 --> 01:40:48,248
And they will not hesitate
to strike back.

1258
01:40:48,316 --> 01:40:50,079
Yes, I know.

1259
01:40:53,155 --> 01:40:56,181
Well, so long as you know.

1260
01:41:00,495 --> 01:41:03,521
Do you think I could have
my present now?

1261
01:41:06,501 --> 01:41:07,627
Yes, of course.

1262
01:41:25,654 --> 01:41:28,885
Take my heart

1263
01:41:32,427 --> 01:41:36,591
And never worry

1264
01:41:38,800 --> 01:41:42,201
Evil tongues will mock

1265
01:41:42,270 --> 01:41:45,137
We'll mock in turn

1266
01:41:45,207 --> 01:41:49,644
For my heart
is my gift to thee

1267
01:41:52,948 --> 01:41:55,883
Have not a care

1268
01:41:57,852 --> 01:41:59,752
Never worry

1269
01:41:59,821 --> 01:42:01,220
Stay, Ulrick, stay.

1270
01:42:01,289 --> 01:42:02,654
Please.

1271
01:42:02,724 --> 01:42:04,521
Marry one of
these lovely young women.

1272
01:42:04,593 --> 01:42:06,390
I know there's at least one left.

1273
01:42:06,461 --> 01:42:08,258
I'll bring God's word
to my homeland.

1274
01:42:08,330 --> 01:42:10,798
No, this is not a good time.
No prince can protect you there.

1275
01:42:10,865 --> 01:42:13,060
I want the Dutch people to know

1276
01:42:13,134 --> 01:42:16,035
what I experienced when I
read His word for the first time.

1277
01:42:20,175 --> 01:42:21,437
Then God be with you.

1278
01:42:25,680 --> 01:42:27,170
And with you, Martin.

1279
01:42:33,355 --> 01:42:36,950
You left so quickly,
I feared it was my singing.

1280
01:42:37,025 --> 01:42:38,356
If only it were.

1281
01:42:39,361 --> 01:42:40,555
Look at him.

1282
01:42:40,629 --> 01:42:43,063
He goes to his fate,
hurrying like a bridegroom.

1283
01:42:43,131 --> 01:42:45,861
Not all bridegrooms
are so fleet.

1284
01:42:48,136 --> 01:42:51,071
I would not say the bachelors
of Wittenberg have been tardy.

1285
01:42:51,139 --> 01:42:52,128
True.

